<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The preface or introduction to a discourse, poem, or
performance; <as>as, the <ex>prologue</ex> of Chaucer's
⟦ldquo⟧Canterbury Tales;⟦rdquo⟧</as> esp., a discourse or poem spoken
before a dramatic performance</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who delivers a prologue.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prologue</ent>⟦br⟧

